parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the check engine light comes on
the dashboard warning indicators illuminate
the power steering seizes operation
and the battery warning indicator flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to become stuck or fall out of the ignition, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck or falls out of the ignition
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the key can be removed without turning off the ignition
and the ignition cylinder needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The doors do not unlock properly
the horn remains engaged
the alarm system malfunctions
and the body control module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls while driving
the check engine light comes on
and the throttle body needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the "Check Engine" light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and there may be a tapping or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the "Check Engine" light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and there may be a loud noise or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the "Check Engine" light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and there may be a loud noise or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the "Check Engine" light comes on
the vehicle loses power
and there may be a fuel leak or strange smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle makes loud noises or produces excessive smoke
and the transmission fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
and the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission safety issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle can be shifted into gear without pressing the brake pedal
the gear lever comes unattached from the floor assembly while driving
and the transmission can downshift very hard in stop-and-go driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle seal failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Leaking right axle seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: All-Wheel Drive system failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The All-Wheel Drive system shuts off to protect the system from overheating
and the vehicle can become stuck in a particular gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the steering wheel to seize, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ignition key releases from the ignition switch
the steering wheel seizes
the ignition switch is hard to turn
the accessory position does not work
the power steering does not activate
smoke is emitted from the steering wheel area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering can cause the steering wheel to become stiff and difficult to maneuver, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The power steering fails
the steering wheel becomes stiff and difficult to maneuver
the vehicle wanders
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle loses control
smoke is emitted from the steering wheel area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause unusual noises, vibrations, and loss of control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises and vibrations from the steering column
the steering wheel makes a noise and vibrates
the steering column is bad and needs replacement
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle wanders.
